Elevator building.Situated midway between Historic Cape May and the "Always Turned On" Atlantic City, Sea Isle City is convenient to all of the attractions that southern New Jersey has to offer. Visitors can enjoy the boardwalks and water parks of Wildwood, Ocean City and Atlantic City, the Cape May Lewes Ferry, the Cape May County Park & Zoo, Historic Cold Spring Village, the Atlantic City casinos, outlet shopping at The Walk, The Pier at Caesars, and Gardner s Basin as well as other area attractions. Once small fishing villages, Sea Isle and Townsend s Inlet on the southern end of the island are now being memorialized by the creation of "Historic Fish Alley," featuring some great bayfront seafood restaurants including Carmen s, Marie s, Mike s, and the Lobster Loft. Presently, Sea Isle offers some of the widest, cleanest beaches in all of New Jersey, attracting families to its shores each summer to enjoy the casual atmosphere of the town. Stroll the oceanfront Promenade or ride the Great American Trolley Company s expanded route, with stops downtown at the new Gillians Funland amusement park, the new bayside boardwalk, and the Excursion Park at JFK Boulevard and the beach. The all new Dealy Field Recreation Complex features tennis, basketball, a skate park, a roller hockey rink, ball fields and a state-of-the-art playground. From Townsend s Inlet to Corson s Inlet, there s something for everyone in Sea Isle City, the Sea and Sand Vacationland!
